pageContext.claim: “What got them was they never thought I was going to release the call. Because I don't like doing that. I don't want to do it. I hope I don't have to do it again -- release phone calls to foreign dignitaries, to foreign leaders. I don't want to do that, John. I don't want to do it again. But I did it with the permission of the Ukrainian government.”
pageContext.analysis: Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelensky said after the release that he had thought Trump was only going to release his side of the conversation.
